lombok.installer.eclipse

Class EclipseLocation

  • java.lang.Object
    • lombok.installer.IdeLocation
      • lombok.installer.eclipse.EclipseLocation
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    JbdsLocation, STSLocation

    public class EclipseLocation
extends IdeLocation
    Represents an Eclipse installation. An instance can figure out if an Eclipse installation has been lombok-ified, and can install and uninstall lombok from the Eclipse installation.

      • uninstall

        public void uninstall()
               throws UninstallException
        Uninstalls lombok from this location. It's a no-op if lombok wasn't there in the first place, and it will remove a half-succeeded lombok installation as well.
        Specified by:
        uninstall in class IdeLocation
        Throws:
        UninstallException - If there's an obvious I/O problem that is preventing installation. bugs in the uninstall code will probably throw other exceptions; this is intentional.

      • install

        public java.lang.String install()
                         throws InstallException
        Install lombok into the Eclipse at this location. If lombok is already there, it is overwritten neatly (upgrade mode).
        Specified by:
        install in class IdeLocation
        Throws:
        InstallException - If there's an obvious I/O problem that is preventing installation. bugs in the install code will probably throw other exceptions; this is intentional.
